void __bang_tiling_2d_b128(void *dst, const void *src, unsigned int n2, unsigned int s2, unsigned int n1, unsigned int s1, unsigned int n7, unsigned int s7, unsigned int n6, unsigned int s6)   Applies 2D tiling operation on <src> for matrix transpose and store the matrix to the <dst>. As shown in Figure The Process of 2 Dimensional Tiling Function , the cells with blue background indicate 64 bytes of data to be copied in each segment, and red blocks indicate basic element unit. In this case, there are 4 segments in the first dimension. <s1> of data in each segment are copied to destination area <n1> times. There are 4 segments in the second dimension. <s2> of data in each segment are copied to destination area <n2> times. Then, calculate matrix transpose based on 128-bit as one element and store the matrix into corresponding segments and dimensions of <dst>. Parameters* [out] dst: The address of output matrix.
* [in] src: The address of input matrix.
* [in] n2: Tiling input iteration 2.
* [in] s2: Tiling input stride 2.
* [in] n1: Tiling input iteration 1.
* [in] s1: Tiling input stride 1.
* [in] n7: Tiling output iteration 7.
* [in] s7: Tiling output stride 7.
